pha Order upon his graduation  He retired from the U S  Air Force as a Force Support officer in 2013  During his Air Force career  Lieutenant Colonel Harrington served in a wide variety of assignments to include deployments in support of Operation ENDURING FREEDOM  He has held various command level assignments  as well as multiple headquarters Air Staff level assignments at the Pentagon  Lieutenant Colonel Harrington is a graduate of the Marine Corps Command and Staff College  Air Command   Staff College  and Squadron Officer School  He also received a Master of Science Degree in International Relations from Troy University in 2002  Lieutenant Colonel Harrington s decorations include the Defense Meritorious Service Medal  the Air Force Meritorious Service Medal  the Air Force Commendation Medal  the Air Force Achievement Medal  the National Defense Service Medal  the Afghanistan Campaign Medal  the Global War on Terrorism Medal  and the NATO medal  Lieutenant Colonel Harrington is married to the former Karon E  Henry of Texarkana  Arkansas  They have two children  Jonathan  VMI Class of 2018  and Erin  13  Office Resources Secretary to BOV BOV Members Public Notice Meeting Schedule   Agenda Committees 2015 2016 Minutes and By Laws   Statement of Governance Code of Ethics   GO46 Terms   Contact Office VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 